radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is edematous and dilated up to 1.2 cm with mural edema and hyperemia. A hyperdensity near the proximal appendix is consistent with represent a fecalith. There is severe right lower quadrant stranding with trace, nonenhancing fluid. Thickening of the cecum and terminal ileum is likely reactive to the adjacent inflammation. Tiny foci of extraluminal air are concerning for perforation.
